For a function that is increasing and concave up on \([a, b]\), the left Riemann sum underestimates the integral, the right sum overestimates it, the trapezoid sum overestimates (since concave up makes the trapezoids lie above the curve), and the midpoint sum underestimates but is more accurate than the left sum.  
Thus the ordering is \(L \leq M \leq T \leq R\).  

\boxed{E}
